---
description: Edge Function handler/service/model layers and middleware presets
globs: supabase/functions/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Backend layers (supabase/functions/)

- `<slug>/index.ts` — `Deno.serve` via middleware presets only (2 lines).
- `<slug>/handler.ts` — HTTP adapter: method check, parse/validate body, auth
  gate via ctx, return JSON. No `.from()`, no business rules.
- `_services/<domain>/<domain>.service.ts` — validation, authorization,
  multi-step workflows, side effects. May serve multiple slugs.
- `_models/<table>.ts` — ALL `.from("<table>")` for that table. No cross-table
  orchestration.
- `_wire/dto/*.dto.ts` — pure wire types, shared with the frontend via
  `@shared/dto/*`. Never duplicate wire types in frontend-only files.
- `_wire/middleware/*` — the internal pipeline (auth, rate limit, access
  control, ownership, CORS, security headers, logging, error boundary).
- `_wire/middleware/presets.ts` — `servePublic`, `serveAuthenticated`,
  `serveWithAccessContext`, `serveWithPermission` — use these in `index.ts`.

## DB clients

- User client (anon key + caller JWT) → RLS applies. Default for user data.
- Service client (service role) → bypasses RLS. ONLY after an explicit
  authorization check in code.
